thread.title: Beaverton High graduate Gigi Stoll ties for 16th in college golf debut with Arizona
thread.title_full: Beaverton High graduate Gigi Stoll ties for 16th in college golf debut with Arizona | OregonLive.com

author: Mike Tokito | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Beaverton High graduate Gigi Stoll ties for 16th in college golf debut with Arizona
text:
Gigi Stoll saved her best round for last in her college golf debut, shooting a 3-under-par 69 to tie for 16th in the Annika Intercollegiate Classic in Orlando, Florida, on Tuesday
Stoll, a freshman from Beaverton High School, helped the Wildcats -- who started the season ranked No. 5 by Golfweek -- finish second behind USC.
After arriving in Tucson last month following a decorated junior career, Stoll played her way onto Arizona's starting roster. In the Annika event -- named after former Arizona golfer Annika Sorenstam -- Stoll started with a 1-over 73 that included an eagle on the par-5 14th, then shot a second-round 72 that included a 33 on the back nine.
Stoll then moved 13 spots up the leaderboard in the final round with a five-birdie, two-bogey 69, closing the tournament with a birdie on the 18th hole. She was one of six golfers in the 60-player field to break 70 in the final round.
"Gigi had an amazing first tournament," coach Laura Ianello told Arizona's sports information staff. "She was very happy with her results. Her putting was spectacular."
Stoll and the Wildcats resume their fall schedule at the two-day Windy City Collegiate that starts Tuesday in Evanston, Illinois.
